  "response": "To prepare for IIT JAM Geology, follow these steps:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Objective multiple-choice questions\n- Total duration: 3 hours\n- Sections: Geology, Geophysics, Geochemistry\n- Negative marking of 1/3 marks\n\n2. Study Materials\n- NCERT textbooks (11th and 12th)\n- Standard reference books\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Online study resources\n\n3. Subject Coverage\n- Physical Geology\n- Structural Geology\n- Mineralogy\n- Petrology\n- Paleontology\n- Stratigraphy\n- Economic Geology\n- Geophysics\n- Geochemistry\n\n4. Recommended Books\n- Press and Siever: Physical Geology\n- Park's Geology\n- Kilty's Mineralogy\n- Holmes' Principles of Physical Geology\n\n5. Preparation Strategy\n- Create a structured study plan\n- Focus on fundamental concepts\n- Practice mock tests\n- Solve previous years' question papers\n- Join online/offline coaching\n- Study consistently\n- Focus on weak areas\n\n6. Additional Tips\n- Time management\n- Regular revision\n- Stay updated with current geological developments\n\nGood luck with your preparation!",
